pipe()
Operators are functions that build on the observables foundation to enable sophisticated manipulation of collections. For example, RxJS defines operators such as map() , filter() , concat() , and flatMap() . You can use pipes to link operators together. Pipes let you combine multiple functions into a single function.The pipe() function takes as its arguments the functions you want to combine, and returns a new function that, when executed, runs the composed functions in sequence.
